# Content Management Guide

## Content Structure
- All content should be placed in `src/content/` using Markdown files
- Use Astro's content collections for organizing different content types
- Keep content separate from presentation logic
- Follow the established content schema for each collection

## Compliance Terminology
- Always use the full format for compliance frameworks:
  - Anti-Money Laundering and Counter-Terrorism Financing – AML/CTF (LAFT – Lavado de Activos y Financiación del Terrorismo)
  - PTEE (PTEE – Plan de Transparencia y Ética Empresarial)
- Maintain consistency across all pages and components
- Use professional, trustworthy language appropriate for compliance services

## Service Descriptions
- Background Checks: Comprehensive background verification services
- Sanction list screening: Screening against international sanctions and PEP databases
- Compliance Services: Implementation of regulatory frameworks and training

## Content Updates
- Update content in the appropriate markdown files
- Ensure content aligns with [INFORMATION.md](mdc:../INFORMATION.md)
- Keep pricing information current and accurate
- Maintain legal compliance in privacy and terms pages

## Quality Assurance
- Validate all links and references
- Ensure content is accessible and clear
- Check for consistency in terminology
- Review content for regulatory accuracy
